result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy J Martins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Contempt/Ct-Nonsummary/Punitive Sanction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 785.03(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:38 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty John Selsing.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to an amended count of contempt of court with probation sentence.  Statement by ADA.  Atty Selsing concurs.  Defendant concurs. Statement by victim.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on the amended charge.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Statement by Amy Erickson.  Sentencing statement by ADA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Selsing.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

SWD, and places the defendant on probation for one year.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent.
-Defendant is to comply with the current family court order in the family case.
-DNA sample.

Court adjourned at 2:51 p.m.
